webpackJsonp([0x6d2019768310],{467:function(A,a){A.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"ourbucketl.ist",author:"Dan Rose & Sophie Mellissa"}},markdownRemark:{id:"C:/Users/danja/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/ourbucketl.ist/src/pages/huaraz/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<blockquote>\n<p>“A lake is the landscape’s most beautiful and expressive feature. It is earth’s eye; looking into which he beholder measures the depth of his own nature.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Henry David Thoreau.</p>\n<h2>Huaraz</h2>\n<p>We took an overnight bus from Lima to Huaraz which left at 21:30 and dumped us in Huaraz at 06:30. Very disorientated and tired, as there was more than one snorer on the bus, we tried to find our hostel, <a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/pe/vacahouse-huaraz-b-b.en-gb.html?aid=357026;label=gog235jc-hotel-XX-pe-vacahouseNhuarazNbNb-unspec-pe-com-L%3Aen-O%3AwindowsS10-B%3Achrome-N%3AXX-S%3Abo-U%3AXX-H%3As;sid=afa45bdb0846f6aa56e77743f5f154c6;dist=0&#x26;sb_price_type=total&#x26;type=total&#x26;">Vacahouse B&#x26;B</a>. However, we didn’t realise there was more than one so around an hour and a cheap motortaxi ride later we managed to find it.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/market-b8addfade9812ff1921c8b8c50626f8d-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Huaraz Market Stall"\n        title="Huaraz Market Stall"\n        src="/static/market-b8addfade9812ff1921c8b8c50626f8d-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/market-b8addfade9812ff1921c8b8c50626f8d-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/market-b8addfade9812ff1921c8b8c50626f8d-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/market-b8addfade9812ff1921c8b8c50626f8d-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Huaraz itself is a small city and it isn’t very touristy, it’s more of a hub for people who are trekking the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huascar%C3%A1n_National_Park">Huascaran National Park</a>. It’s also 3052 meters above sea level, up in the Andes, so we were also conscious to take it easy at first to avoid altitude sickness.</p>\n<h2>Mercado Central de Huaraz</h2>\n<p>Aside from the Plaza de Armas, which was home to a crumbling derelict church, there really wasn’t a lot to see in the city. However, we’d read a few blogs that said the market was worth a visit. We’d been to a few of these in South America and you’d think we’d have learnt our lesson; mostly they contain fruit, strange herbal medicines and smelly unrefridgerated meat. Mercardo Central de Huaraz was no different, we pretty much ran through it holding our noses, stopping for a quick picture of the skinned and gutted guinea pigs.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/guinea-pigs-b22859770b57278c8bd401351c6525a4-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Guinea pigs"\n        title="Guinea pigs"\n        src="/static/guinea-pigs-b22859770b57278c8bd401351c6525a4-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/guinea-pigs-b22859770b57278c8bd401351c6525a4-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/guinea-pigs-b22859770b57278c8bd401351c6525a4-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/guinea-pigs-b22859770b57278c8bd401351c6525a4-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Laguna 69</h2>\n<p>We’d been warned by a friend who had previously done this hike that it was difficult because of the altitude. His exact words were “Laguna 69 trek, it may kill you but worth it”. We booked a tour, mainly because it was easier and the same price as getting there by public transport. We were picked up at 05:00 and taken for breakfast in the middle of nowhere on the way before making our way to the starting point for the hike. Laguna 69 is located in Huascaran National Park and reaches 4604 meters above sea level. We started the hike at around 3800 meters and the first hour was pretty flat, the only challenge was getting around the cows blocking the paths.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/cow-67b2d42bcf91b3730a9d2abae250bfb3-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Cow"\n        title="Cow"\n        src="/static/cow-67b2d42bcf91b3730a9d2abae250bfb3-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/cow-67b2d42bcf91b3730a9d2abae250bfb3-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/cow-67b2d42bcf91b3730a9d2abae250bfb3-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/cow-67b2d42bcf91b3730a9d2abae250bfb3-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Then came our first climb, it was reassuring that people on our tour muttered “it’s hard” as we kept crossing each other on the path. Due to the altitude, we had less oxygen and less energy so every step up was effort. Dan reached the top before me and I thought we’d made it. But it turned out we were about halfway and we’d reached a green coloured lake.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/different-lake-ffbbd5f939e7a6a68b7a0d27170e500c-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Different lake"\n        title="Different lake"\n        src="/static/different-lake-ffbbd5f939e7a6a68b7a0d27170e500c-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/different-lake-ffbbd5f939e7a6a68b7a0d27170e500c-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/different-lake-ffbbd5f939e7a6a68b7a0d27170e500c-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/different-lake-ffbbd5f939e7a6a68b7a0d27170e500c-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>We were graced with a break in climbing, as we crossed along another flat part of the hike before the even steeper climb up to Laguna 69. We managed to spot a Viscacha, which are rodents native to South America, they look like a cross between a rabbit and a squirrel.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/viscacha-c5223e18e80c290649bbb209cc428480-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Viscacha"\n        title="Viscacha"\n        src="/static/viscacha-c5223e18e80c290649bbb209cc428480-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/viscacha-c5223e18e80c290649bbb209cc428480-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/viscacha-c5223e18e80c290649bbb209cc428480-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/viscacha-c5223e18e80c290649bbb209cc428480-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The last climb up was even more effort, we and everyone who’d kept our pace, had to keep stopping every 4-5 meters to catch their breath. The altitude made the hike so much harder, but we got a final burst of energy when a guide told us we were about five minutes from the top.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/flowers-5f32271f33b384bb692216eb9c18e7c4-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Flowers"\n        title="flowers"\n        src="/static/flowers-5f32271f33b384bb692216eb9c18e7c4-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/flowers-5f32271f33b384bb692216eb9c18e7c4-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/flowers-5f32271f33b384bb692216eb9c18e7c4-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/flowers-5f32271f33b384bb692216eb9c18e7c4-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>We were so pleased when we saw the blue water and we knew we’d made it. We were told it would take us around three hours to get to the top but we did it in two hours and forty five minutes, it took some of the others three and a half hours to get to the top. We took lots of photo’s and ate our picnic lunch just as it started to hail, ready for the two hour walk back down. Because it had been raining whilst we were at the top, the paths on the way down had turned into streams but we didn’t care as the 7km walk down was so much easier than the climb up.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/rain-f60c6487a5025508bd227443dd55f354-769ec.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 900px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Rain"\n        title="Rain"\n        src="/static/rain-f60c6487a5025508bd227443dd55f354-769ec.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/rain-f60c6487a5025508bd227443dd55f354-d9ef2.jpg 225w,\n/static/rain-f60c6487a5025508bd227443dd55f354-ac97c.jpg 450w,\n/static/rain-f60c6487a5025508bd227443dd55f354-769ec.jpg 900w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Our Verdict on Huaraz</h2>\n<p>We mainly visited Huaraz to hike to Laguna 69 and we were glad we did. It was the hardest hike we’d done (ever) but it was worth it for the views of the sapphire blue lake and the stunning scenery in Huascaran National Park.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Huaraz, Peru",date:"May 20, 2018",image:{childImageSharp:{sizes:{base64:"data:image/jpeg;base64,",aspectRatio:1.7777777777777777,src:"/static/laguna-69-1643728e662aa934ea4b5fb12268af98-47774.jpg",srcSet:"/static/laguna-69-1643728e662aa934ea4b5fb12268af98-45ad6.jpg 480w,\n/static/laguna-69-1643728e662aa934ea4b5fb12268af98-e2fcf.jpg 960w,\n/static/laguna-69-1643728e662aa934ea4b5fb12268af98-47774.jpg 1920w",sizes:"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"}}}}}},pathContext:{slug:"/huaraz/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/ica/"},frontmatter:{title:"Ica, Peru"}},next:{fields:{slug:"/huanchaco/"},frontmatter:{title:"Huanchaco, Peru"}}}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---huaraz-5a46c958a74d2abdfcad.js.map